  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "System Designer",
  "description": "<p>Are you passionate about the latest AV / UC technologies? Do you pride yourself on being meticulous and have a fine eye for detail? Are you a fast learner and possess a deep passion on seeing your creation and design into execution?  Are you looking for an engineering job that combines your excellent AV knowledge with your enthusiasm about the latest AV technologies in the market?</p>\n<p>If so, come join our team! We believe in delivering excellence and if you share the same motto, we’ll be a great fit together. We promise you a friendly work environment and the opportunity to grow your career.</p>\n<p><strong>The Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Provide technical expertise and assist in the design, recommendation and evaluation of AV system setup.</li>\n  <li>Create A/V designs (to include A/V control, video, audio, and networking schematics) as part of engineering design Packages.</li>\n  <li>Generate Build of Materials (BOM)</li>\n  <li>Generate A/V proposals</li>\n  <li>Organize and prepare demonstration of proposed solutions to customers.</li>\n  <li>Participate in project meetings with customers and representatives.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate the design review and change process with Project Managers, Sales team and customers.</li>\n  <li>Keep abreast of the latest technologies in the AV industry.</li>\n  <li>Generate functional connection-level drawings for audio, video, control and communications systems.</li>\n  <li>Perform Site Survey/Evaluation when required.</li>\n  <li>Attend site coordination meeting when required</li>\n  <li>Support turnover of the completed installations to the Clients to include User acceptance and training.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>The Pre-Requisites:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>At least 2 years of experience working in an AV industry as a System Designer.</li>\n  <li>Knowledge and design experience with the following manufacturers: Crestron, Extron, AMX, Polycom, Biamp, Clearone, QSC, Cisco.</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of AutoCAD program</li>\n  <li>Relevant recognized industry certifications will be an added advantage (e.g. CTS)</li>\n  <li>Strong communication and interpersonal skills.</li>\n  <li>Good team player and able to work independently.</li>\n  <li>Must be organized, able to multi-task, and work under pressure to meet tight deadlines.</li>\n  <li>Must be a detailed, patient and fast worker</li>\n  <li>Drive to exceed expectations and in delivering excellence.</li>\n</ul>",
